<paragraph id="IAS19_140" base="F16152230" principles="no"><paranum>140</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IASÂ 19"/><data name="paranum" value="140"/></prolog><body><p id="IAS19_P0625">An entity shall provide a reconciliation from the opening balance to the closing balance for each of the following, if applicable:</p><ol id="IAS19_L0078" base="F16152232" type="lower-alpha"><li id="IAS19_140_a"><li_value>(a)</li_value> <p id="IAS19_P0626" base="F16152233">the <xref base="F16149650" href="IAS19_0003.dita#IAS19_0003/IAS19_UN0010">net defined benefit liability (asset)<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0253"/></ph></xref>, showing separate reconciliations for:</p> <ol id="IAS19_L0079" base="F16152678" type="lower-roman"><li id="IAS19_140_a_i"><li_value>(i)</li_value> <p id="IAS19_P0627" base="F16152679"><xref base="F16149665" href="IAS19_0003.dita#IAS19_0003/IAS19_UN0014">plan assets<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0290"/></ph></xref>.</p></li><li id="IAS19_140_a_ii"><li_value>(ii)</li_value> <p id="IAS19_P0628" base="F16152681">the <xref base="F16149663" href="IAS19_0003.dita#IAS19_0003/IAS19_UN0013">present value of the defined benefit obligation<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0298"/></ph></xref>.</p></li><li id="IAS19_140_a_iii"><li_value>(iii)</li_value> <p id="IAS19_P0629" base="F16152683">the effect of the <xref base="F16149661" href="IAS19_0003.dita#IAS19_0003/IAS19_UN0012">asset ceiling<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0016"/></ph></xref>.</p></li></ol></li><li id="IAS19_140_b"><li_value>(b)</li_value> <p id="IAS19_P0630" base="F16152685">any reimbursement rights. An entity shall also describe the relationship between any reimbursement right and the related obligation.</p></li></ol></body></paragraph>